page.title: 02ECOLOGY IN NORTH BUCKS
page.content: North Bucks is a very rural with a rich ecology. In the 12km area there are many types of plants and animals.There is a nature reserve, called Hyde Lane,run by BBONT.This has a lake surrounded by a deciduous wood and marshland.The lake is used for fishing,however a permit or pass is required.The fishing rights are held by the Buckingham and District Angling Association.{ The{wildlife}in and around Hyde Lane nature reserve includes{fish}e.g.pike, rainbow trout,tench,perch and chubb. There are also{birds}which include herons,coots,canada geese,grebes, kingfishers and moorhens as well as the more common birds such as sparrows and starlings.{Animals}include badgers, rabbits, foxes, stoats and weasles.
